Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks. Place on a lined #baking tray{}. Toss with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a drizzle of @oil{}.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%grams}.

When the sweet potato has been cooking for ~{10%minutes}, add the tomatoes to the tray with a drizzle of oil. Mix together and return to the top shelf for the remaining cooking time, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Trim the @courgette{1} then slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(cloves) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

When hot, add the onion and courgette and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, tear the @baguette{2} into small, bite-sized croutons.

Add the croutons to a separate lined baking tray with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of @salt{}.

Toss to coat and spread out in a single layer.

Bake on the middle shelf of the oven until crispy and golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Give the tray a shake halfway through.

> TIP: Watch croutons carefully so they don't burn!

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{} mix @oil{1%tbsp} together with the @red wine vinegar{1%sachet}, @honey{1%sachet} and @mayo{2%sachets}.

Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, mix well and set aside.

When the onion and courgette have softened, stir in the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more.

Remove from the heat and add to the bowl with the dressing.

When ready, remove the veg and croutons from the oven, add to the bowl and gently mix.

Let everything sit for a couple of mins to allow the croutons to absorb the flavours.

Carefully fold the @salad leaves{40%grams} into the bowl with the veg and croutons.

Divide your warm veg salad between plates.

Finish everything with a generous crumble of @Greek style cheese{100%grams}.

> This warm veg salad is adorned with all sorts of wonderful things. Crispy croutons, softened onion and salty Greek style cheese are just a few factors in this delicious and healthy dish.